dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: Applicable_Records
class.description: The records to which this state applies.

class.title: Calibration_Reference
class.description: Contains a reference to a document that describes the energy calibration for the product.

class.title: Detector
class.description: Specifies a single detector which was active at the time of observation.

class.title: Detectors
class.description: Specifies which detectors were active on an instrument at the time of observation.

class.title: Energy_Calibration
class.description: Specifies methods and data used to determine the pulse height in energy units (e.g. MeV) for each channel of a pulse height spectrum.

class.title: First_Count
class.description: Defines the records to which this state applies by identifying the first record (inclusive), and the number of contiguous records, including the first.

class.title: First_Last
class.description: Defines the first and last records for which this state applies. The record numbers are one-based and inclusive.

class.title: Instrument_Settings
class.description: This class specifies instrument settings. Instrument settings may be driven via a state table, which may be associated with specific observations within the data product, either by directly indicating those records, or indicating the observation times at which certain states apply.

class.title: NucSpec_Observation_Properties
class.description: This class specifies properties pertaining to a nuclear spectroscopy observation.

class.title: Observing_Condition
class.description: Describes the times that the activity affecting nuclear spectroscopy observations was in effect, along with the sources of the activity, if applicable.

class.title: Observing_Conditions
class.description: Describes activity that may affect nuclear spectroscopy observations.

class.title: Polynomial
class.description: The pulse height in energy units (e.g. MeV) is determined for a given channel number using the polynomial: H(x) = a0 + a1 x + a2 x^2 + ..., where H is pulse height with energy units and x is channel number.

class.title: Polynomial_Term
class.description: Describes a single term in the polynomial function.

class.title: State_Table
class.description: Specifies an additional look-up table that provides additional information about specific observations within the product.

class.title: State_Table_Entry
class.description: Associates individual observations in the data product with a record in the state table, providing additonal information on those observations.

class.title: State_Time
class.description: The time during which this state was applicable. The state table entry is applicable to records in the referenced data table if the time of the data record, as given by state_time_field_name, is between the start time and stop time given in State_Time.

class.title: Time_Range_ET
class.description: Ephemeris time, as defined by the referenced field, for the first and last science data records for a temporally contiguous block of records with the same state or affected by the same conditions. These records need not be contiguous within the file, but there must be no records with a different state between the start and stop time.

class.title: Time_Range_SCLK
class.description: Spacecraft clock time in ticks since spacecraft clock start for the first and last science data records for a temporally contiguous block of records with the same state or affected by the same conditions. These records need not be contiguous within the file, but there must be no records with a different state between the start and stop time.

class.title: Time_Range_UTC
class.description: Universal Coordinated Time for the first and last science data records for a temporally contiguous block of records with the same state or affected by the same conditions. These records need not be contiguous within the file, but there must be no records with a different state between the start and stop time.

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: Any notes about the state at the time of observation.

attribute.title: description
attribute.description: A description for the detector.

attribute.title: name
attribute.description: The name of the detector.

attribute.title: first_record
attribute.description: The first record for which the state applies, inclusive.

attribute.title: record_count
attribute.description: The number of consecutive records, including the first, for which this state applies.

attribute.title: first_record
attribute.description: The first record for which the state applies, inclusive.

attribute.title: last_record
attribute.description: The last record for which this state applies, inclusive.

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: Any notes about the state at the time of observation.

attribute.title: condition_active
attribute.description: A flag indicating whether the condition was in effect at the given time.

attribute.title: condition_source
attribute.description: A string identifying the source of the condition at the given time.

attribute.title: condition_type
attribute.description: Remarks about the containing object.

attribute.title: coefficient
attribute.description: The coefficient of a single term of the polynomial relating channel number to pulse height.

attribute.title: order
attribute.description: The order of a single term of the polynomial relating channel number to pulse height.

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: Any notes about the state at the time of observation.

attribute.title: state_index
attribute.description: The state_index points to a row of a look up table containing the instrument settings.

attribute.title: state_time_field_name
attribute.description: The name of the field in the referenced data table that contains the time.

attribute.title: et_start
attribute.description: The earliest ephemeris time, as defined by the referenced field, for which this state or condition is applicable.

attribute.title: et_stop
attribute.description: The latest ephemeris time, as defined by the referenced field, for which this state or condition is applicable.

attribute.title: sclk_start_time
attribute.description: The earliest spacecraft clock time, in ticks since spacecraft clock start, for which this state or condition is applicable.

attribute.title: sclk_stop_time
attribute.description: The latest spacecraft clock time, in ticks since spacecraft clock start, for which this state or condition is applicable.

attribute.title: utc_start_time
attribute.description: The earliest Universal Coordinated Time for which this state or condition is applicable.

attribute.title: utc_stop_time
attribute.description: The earliest Universal Coordinated Time for which this state or condition is applicable.
